
[1]antispasmodic

   ANTISPASMOD'IC, a. [Gr. against, and from to draw.]

   Opposing spasm; resisting convulsions; as anodynes.

   ANTISPASMOD'IC, n. A remedy for spasm or convulsions, as opium, balsam
               of Peru, and the essential oils of vegetables.
